of the New World to the wars in Afghanistan, Iraq, and beyond. A history of the present crisis, Security and Terror also examines how that history has been registered and reckoned with in significant works of contemporary fiction and theory—in novels by Teju Cole, Mohsin Hamid, Junot Díaz, and Roberto Bolaño, and in the critical interventions of Jean Baudrillard, Giorgio Agamben, Judith Butler, Michael Hardt and Antonio Negri, and others. In this richly interdisciplinary inquiry, Jelly-Schapiro reveals how the erasure of colonial pasts enables the perpetual reproduction of colonial culture.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 04. Okt 2022) 0aImperialism. 0aInternational relations and terrorismzUnited States. 0aNational securityzUnited States. 0aTerrorismzUnited States. 0aWar on Terrorism, 2001-2009, in literature. 0aWar on Terrorism, 2001-2009. 7aHISTORY / United States / 20th Century.2bisacsh  a1492.  a9/11.  aafghanistan.  aamerican history.  abahamas.  acapitalist.  achristopher columbus.  acolonial.  acolonialism.  acolonization.  acrisis.  acuba.  aerasure.  aexplorer.  agenealogy.  ahispaniola.  ainterdisciplinary.  airaq.  ajunot diaz.  aliterature.  amoshin hamid.  anew world.  anorth america.  anorth american history.  aphilosophy.  apolitics.  apost colonial.  aroberto bolano.  asecurity.  aseptember 11th.  asettlers.  ateju cole.  aterror.  aunited states history.  aus history.  awar on terror.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2018z97831106676770 cprintz978052029537740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520968158423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520968158/original  a978-3-11-066767-7  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 